Only an option when cold food and time is not an issue. I've ordered twice and waited over two hours for each order. The majority of that has been waiting while the driver sits outside another restaurant while my food is ready and getting cold. Bear in mind both times the restaurant was 2.5km away. Bolt Foods process flow is backwards. The app seems to call the driver to the restaurant as soon as the order is placed. The driver will then drive to the restaurant immediately and wait around for half an hour before picking up another order (possibly on a different app) and then abandoning my order to go wait at the next restaurant. By this time my order will become ready and I will sit and watch the estimated time tick up while the driver zips around the city in the opposite direction. If I zoom in they will always be stationary outside other popular restaurants. I've used Bolt twice now and had to watch my screen for two hours each time while the status says 'Your courier is picking up your order' while I can literally see him waiting at KFC across town. Presumably picking up a different order for a different app. My issue is not with the drivers but with the fact that Bolt should only offer the gig and match drivers once the order is ready or at least after the restaurant has been preparing it for awhile.
replyContent: Hi, Matthew! We are currently working on ways to ensure that you get your orders at the earliest time possible. Kindly reach out to us on your Bolt app or send an email to za-food@bolt.eu so that we may address your concerns with regard to the delivery time for your orders.

content: The application is quite OK with a user interface you would expect and might be used to. It works just fine and contrary to some other similar apps doesn't lie about prices and delivery fees. Its search function is very limited and basically useless unless you know the exact name of the venue you are searching for. It has the best-in-class order tracking that actually works. The service itself is the fastest and cheapest at my location (Prague, Czech Rep.) and is very reliable. Overall this is the best food delivery service available in the city ...as long as everything goes as expected. Once something goes wrong you are screwed. There is no support whatsoever. It is even stated in their terms and conditions that they are only an online market and that they only care about your money. No guarantees, no communication. I once tried to complain about my order being delivered incomplete and they never even responded. It seems to be a fire-and-forget autonomous system without any supervision and support. Update: The last time I needed to contact the support, it actually worked and I was instantly refunded 100% of the order price.
replyContent: Hi there, David! Thank you for your complex feedback. Our support is available from early morning to late evening every day in the app or via cz-food@bolt.eu. We're fluent in Czech, too. Please, contact our support about your experience. We would like to make sure that it will not happen again.
